The paper deals with the problem of scalable indexing of local features for visual instance search, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of a scalable disk-based index, which is a topic that falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper presents a detailed performance evaluation, which involves measuring insertion throughput and scalability, and these are topics that fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and multimedia (cs.MM).
